column37: Most that are not beneficial to me is because of two major factors: COVID + I wasn't raised in America. So, figuring out college is hard for me, especially classes, counseling, what classes to take first, what should I do next.. the educational system is completely different from where I came from, so I have this huge difficulty to understand it. Also.. because of Covid, it's hard to simply show up at school's front desk and ask to speak to someone that is available to answers basic questions of: how does school/classes/college/university work here? I do read a lot about it, but there are still things that don't make sense. Or classes that I still wonder if I really need it or not. Or if they are a pre-rec or not. Or if that's is a real major or not. Simple things. But yeah, those two major factors make me feel disconnected to school and somehow not really involved and into what's going on.

column24: Access to affordable private tutors.  SWC online tutoring hasn't met or helpful in tutoring me.  The last two sessions 30 minutes were wasted because the tutor was not able to immediately help in the subject matter because she needed to look up those information.  The last tutoring session, she wasted 30 minutes even though I kept reminding her to start the tutoring.  Each session is only 45 minutes long.  I got two appts with her so it's 1 hour and 30 minutes.  However, 30 minutes she just won't start.  This is not ok.  I went for help and I'm not getting it.  I failed Lecture Exam 3.  If need resources, hiring a private tutor is more beneficial than this.
column37: I am aware of SWC Online Tutoring session and even attend several, but I didn't get the help that I needed.  The last two, 1 for 45 minutes, and the other for 1 1/2 hours (I got two appts in one day) didn't help me, and in fact wasted my time.  As I mentioned above, at least 30 minutes into the tutoring session was not tutoring.  Either the tutor wasted 30 minutes to look up information, or wouldn't begin (even though she was online) until 30 minutes later.  Unacceptable.  I wanted to succeed that's why I went to tutoring.
